 Contribution: Establishes backpropagation as a foundational mechanism for training neural networks, directly supporting the role of recursive feedback in validating advanced systems like FractiScope.
4. OpenAI (2023). GPT-4 Technical Report.
 Contribution: Provides performance benchmarks for ChatGPT, validating the 10–100 FPUs range in FractiPower for structured, repetitive tasks.
5. Mendez, P. L. (2021). The Cognitive Divide Between Humans and Digital Intelligence Systems: Bridging the Gap.
 Contribution: Defines the complementary strengths of human and digital intelligence systems, serving as a basis for FractiPower’s human baseline and its extensions to AI and fractal systems.
6. Wolfram, S. (2002). A New Kind of Science.
 Contribution: Explores computational systems based on simple rules that yield complex behavior, reinforcing the adaptability and scalability of fractal intelligence systems like FractiScope.
7. Silver, D., Schrittwieser, J., Simonyan, K., et al. (2017). Mastering the Game of Go Without Human Knowledge. Nature, 550(7676), 354–359.
