11. Anderson, P. W. (1972). More Is Different: Broken Symmetry and the Nature of the Hierarchical Structure of Science. Science, 177(4047), 393–396.
 Contribution: Validates the emergent properties of hierarchical systems, aligning with FractiScope’s ability to integrate solutions across nested layers.
12. Hawking, S. (1988). A Brief History of Time: From the Big Bang to Black Holes.
 Contribution: Explores the universal patterns that govern physical and cognitive systems, supporting FractiScope’s harmonic alignment and scalability.
13. Penrose, R. (1989). The Emperor's New Mind.
